frameDefinitions: The Means action by which a deprofiled agent (the Protagonist) has attempted to achieve a Goal, is finished and the actual outcome of the Means action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Protagonist's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
The Hearer receives a Message or communication on a particular Topic.
A Speaker interprets a written Text and speaks the contents, usually to an Addressee.
The Reader attends to a Text to process its information.
In this frame an Ingestor takes a Substance into his or her body.
A Reader visually examines a Text, typically in a linear order, to understand its content.
frameExamples: Teenage fans first <t>heard</t> about the tragedy on a popular radio show.
I do think they <t>read</t> to them when they are little. INI

You should refrain from <t>taking</t> vodka up the nose.
